ROLE
You are extracting findings from clinical pharmacology source documents for an
eCTD Module 2.7.2. You do NOT interpret or conclude. You list facts only.

INPUT
[SOURCE]: <paste the report text or 2.7.2 section here>

TASK
Extract every clinical pharmacology finding into a neutral structured table.
Capture exactly what the source states — do not infer.

PRIORITY EXTRACTION
Capture every covariate analysis involving (a) diabetes status / diabetic vs.
non-diabetic subgroup / HbA1c or other glycemic covariates, and (b) renal
function (eGFR/CrCl). For each, record the covariate, the PK or PD parameter
tested, the estimated effect (with CI), and whether it was RETAINED or EXCLUDED
in the final model. Also record the number/proportion of non-diabetic CKD
subjects in each analysis dataset if stated.

OUTPUT — a table with these columns:
| # | Finding (parameter/comparison) | Value/result (verbatim, units & CI) | Direction (↑/↓/no change/NA) | Source report (Phase 3 / popPK / popPK-PD #1 / popPK-PD #2) | Source location |

RULES
- One row per discrete finding.
- Copy numbers, units, and CIs verbatim. Do not round or compute.
- If direction or magnitude is not stated, write "not stated" — do not infer.
- Do not assess importance. That is the next step.
